main event: A woman in Walker, Minnesota reported sighting a bright, yellowish star-like object that appeared to move across the sky over the course of about 30 minutes on February 6, 1968.
interesting points: The object appeared to stop and hover at times, and also seemed to zip across the sky to higher altitudes.
The object was described as brighter than the brightest stars, and appeared translucent or horizontal at times, making its exact shape difficult to determine.
The witness reported the object disappeared instantaneously at one point.
The witness could not estimate the speed of the object, but said it appeared to move at a very high speed, possibly around 500 mph.
No photographs were taken, but the witness did provide a hand-drawn sketch showing the object's movement and changing appearance.
